fields.value: Replication Data for "Complex near-surface rheology inferred from the response of greater Tokyo to strong ground motions"

dsDescriptionValue.value:
Single-station cross-correlation (SC) functions for Viens et al. (2018, submitted to JGR).
Each file (.mat Matlab structure) contains the SC functions (acausal and causal parts, -5 to 5 s time lag with a 200 Hz sampling rate: 2001 data points for each 15-min SC function) for one MeSO-net station, computed every 15-min from February, 20, 2011 to May, 11, 2011:
dat.station -> Station name
dat.filter -> Filter applied before computing the SC functions
dat.t_step -> Time step (SC functions computed every 15 min)
dat.delta -> Sampling rate in Hz
dat.UN -> SC functions computed from the vertical and North-South components
dat.UE -> SC functions computed from the vertical and East-West components
dat.ref_UN -> Reference SC functions computed from the vertical and North-South components
dat.ref_UE -> Reference SC functions computed from the vertical and East-West components
The Station_coordinates.mat file contains the coordinates of each station (latitude and longitude).
